Find the x-intercept of the line normal to the tangent line of $y = cos x "at" x = pi/3$

$m = - 1 / (- sin pi / 3)$

$m = 2 / sqrt(3)$

$cos pi / 3 = 2 / sqrt(3) pi / 3 + b$

$b = 1/2 - (2 pi) / (3 sqrt(3))$

$y = 2 / sqrt(3) x + 1/2 - (2 pi) / (3 sqrt(3))$

$0 = 2 / sqrt(3) x + 1/2 - (2 pi) / (3 sqrt(3))$

$x = pi / 3 - sqrt(3)/4$
